snippet: Iran’s state television said the country used liquid fuel for the first time to launch the rocket, named Pajohesh, meaning “research” in Farsi.
abstract: Iran says it has successfully launched a monkey into space for the second time, part of ambitious rocket program aimed at manned spaceflight.
lead_paragraph: Iran’s state television said the country used liquid fuel for the first time to launch the rocket, named Pajohesh, meaning “research” in Farsi.

headline.main: Iran Reports Sending Another Monkey Into Space
headline.print_headline: Iran Reports Successfully Sending Another Monkey Into Space
